# 2.8 Advanced String Formatting

## Width

```python
f"{name:10}"
```

## Alignment

```python
f"{name:<10}"   # Left
f"{name:>10}"   # Right
f"{name:^10}"   # Center
```

## Fill Characters

```python
f"{9:0>4}"      # 0009
f"{name:*^10}"
```

## Floating Precision

```python
f"{price:.2f}"
f"{price:,.2f}"
```

---

# 2.9 String Slicing

## Basic Slicing

```python
text[start:end]
```

## Common Examples

```python
text[0:5]     # First 5 characters
text[:5]      # Same as above
text[5:]      # From index 5 to end
text[:-1]     # Everything except last character
text[::2]     # Every other character
text[::-1]    # Reverse string
```

## Rules

- Start index is included.
- End index is excluded.
- Slicing returns a new string.

