# 2.10 String Methods

## Search and Replace

```python
text.replace("old", "new")
text.find("x")
text.rfind("x")
text.count("x")
```

## Membership

```python
"cat" in text
"dog" not in text
```

## Boolean Methods

```python
text.isalnum()
text.isdigit()
text.islower()
text.isupper()
text.isspace()
text.startswith("http")
text.endswith(".txt")
```

## Case and Cleanup

```python
text.lower()
text.upper()
text.capitalize()
text.title()
text.strip()
```

## Common Input Cleanup

```python
name = input().strip().lower()
```

## Important Rule

- Use `==` to compare strings.
- Do not use `is`.

